gomodel:SYNGO_4195  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: Description in Figure 5 legend.\nFig. 5. \"Electron micrographs showing trkB immunoreactivity over postsynaptic densities(PSDs). Anti-trkBout antisera were used. In (A) and other pan-els, curved arrows point to immunoreactive postsynaptic densities(PSDs) and open arrows point to unlabeled PSDs and arrowheads point to symmetric synaptic junctions. \"\n- \"Peroxidase reaction product accumulated over PSDs of spines (Figs. 5A-D).\"\n\n19/01/2021 Dnyanada:\nFigure 4: Western blot analysis using anti-trkBin reveals the full-length trkB and several minor bands in the PSD (Fig. 4A). The bands were abolished using antibodies preadsorbed with the peptide antigens (Fig.4B), indicating specificity of the immunoreaction.. Experimental description: Materials and Methods\nExperimental Animals and Subcellular Fractions\nSprague-Dawley rats were used." ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0001-6194-9648" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0001-5518-6584" ;
        dc:date           "2021-01-19" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_CC_4195" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10116" .

